  <title>Planet Earth</title>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Planet Earth — Quick Guide</h1>
  <p>Our planet is full of incredible records, species, and facts. Here is a quick guide using lists!</p>

  <h2>Steps to Protect Our Planet:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Switch off lights when you leave a room</li>
    <li>Use a reusable water bottle every day</li>
    <li>Walk or cycle instead of travelling by car</li>
    <li>Plant a tree in your neighbourhood</li>
    <li>Spread awareness — talk to your friends!</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Incredible Natural Wonders:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Amazon Rainforest — home to 10% of all species on Earth</li>
    <li>Great Barrier Reef — the largest coral reef, visible from space</li>
    <li>Mount Everest — the highest point on Earth at 8,849 metres</li>
    <li>Sahara Desert — the largest hot desert in the world</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Key Terms:</h2>
  <dl>
    <dt>Climate Change</dt>
    <dd>Long-term shifts in global temperature caused by human activity</dd>

    <dt>Renewable Energy</dt>
    <dd>Energy from natural sources like sunlight and wind that never run out</dd>

    <dt>Biodiversity</dt>
    <dd>The variety of all living species on Earth</dd>
  </dl>

</body>
</html>
